long_desc.thetext:
Go to http://demo.qooxdoo.org/current/widgetbrowser and check the "disabled" checkbox. Click in a disabled text field and write some greetings in it.

Or create a minimum application just containing:

8<-------------------------------------------
var tf = new qx.ui.form.TextField("foobar");
tf.setEnabled(false);
var doc = this.getRoot();
doc.add(tf, {top: 0, left: 0});
8<-------------------------------------------

You get a disabled TextField that can be edited.

I can't see this behaviour in Firefox, etc.
